        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8562.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from H. A. Huxley and T. H. Huxley, 17 October 1872</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD enclosed a cheque for £100; it is recorded in his Account books–cash account (Down House MS) under the heading ‘Huxley present’ for 16 October 1872. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2486.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Thomas Henry Huxley</ref> had bought a house at 4 Marlborough Place, London in June 1872 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1979.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">A. Desmond 1994–7</ref>, 2: 43).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Huxley had been suffering ill health since the summer (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1979.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">A. Desmond 1994–7</ref>, 2: 43).</note>
